        <p id="tribute-info">Dr. Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam was born on October 15, 1931, in Rameswaram, Tamil Nadu. He rose from humble beginnings to become one of India's most respected scientists and the 11th President of India, serving from 2002 to 2007. His journey exemplifies perseverance, intellect, and a commitment to education and scientific advancement.On the 10th anniversary of his passing on July 27, 2025, Prime Minister Narendra Modi and other leaders paid tribute to Dr. Kalam, highlighting his exemplary dedication to the nation and his motivational influence on the youth. Modi described him as an "inspiring visionary" whose thoughts continue to guide and inspire. Dr. Kalam's legacy as a leader who dedicated his life to national service and scientific progress remains relevant today, serving as a beacon of hope and inspiration for future generations.</p>
